# ── Bot Worker (root: wrangler.toml + .dev.vars / wrangler secret) ─────────────
# DISCORD_TOKEN              — Bot token (secret; never commit)
# DISCORD_PUBLIC_KEY         — Interactions verification (Developer Portal)
# DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID     — Application id
# ADMIN_CHANNEL_ID           — Admin review channel
# VOTING_CHANNEL_ID          — Announcements / legacy vote channel
# BLOG_CHANNEL_ID            — Optional blog announcements
# DEVELOPER_CHALLENGES_CHANNEL_ID
# HACKER_CHALLENGES_CHANNEL_ID
# ADMIN_ROLE_ID
# GITHUB_TOKEN               — Optional: richer /pulse
# CLAUDE_API_KEY             — Optional: monthly challenge generation (Anthropic)
# SESSION_SECRET             — Same value as auth Worker; verifies hns_session on API (when wired)

# ── Auth Worker (/auth/wrangler.toml + secrets) ───────────────────────────────
# BASE_URL                   — Public site origin, e.g. https://hns.gg
# DISCORD_GUILD_ID           — Server snowflake (same as NEXT_PUBLIC_DISCORD_GUILD_ID)
# DISCORD_CLIENT_ID          — OAuth2 application client id
# DISCORD_CLIENT_SECRET      — wrangler secret put DISCORD_CLIENT_SECRET
# SESSION_SECRET             — Long random string; signs cookies & encrypts stored Discord token
# COOKIE_DOMAIN              — Optional; e.g. .hns.gg for shared subdomain cookies

# ── Website (see website/.env.example) ────────────────────────────────────────
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_URL, NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL, HNS_AUTH_WORKER_URL (or zone route /auth/*),
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DISCORD_GUILD_ID, NEXT_PUBLIC_DISCORD_CLIENT_ID
